 from the asteroid and go\ninto a slightly smaller orbit than that of the asteroid. If our interpretation\nis correct, we can use the drift rate to determine the mass of the asteroid.\nUnder that scenario, we find that the mass of the asteroid is M_a ~ = 10^23\ngrams, or about 1/10th the mass of Ceres, with an uncertainty of about a factor\nof 2.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Feb 2016 23:04:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 19 Mar 2016 00:53:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
