trsim$100\\%, reaching $\\gtrsim$1000\\% for low temperatures (T$\\lesssim$500K)\nand high pressures (P$\\gtrsim$1 atm). The effect is higher still for self\nbroadening. We generate a homogeneous database of absorption cross sections of\nmolecules of relevance to exoplanetary atmospheres for which high temperature\nline lists are available, particularly H$_2$O, CO, CH$_4$, CO$_2$, HCN, and\nNH$_3$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Feb 2016 00:11:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-17"}
