entral Limit Theorem, the higher moments are only felt in the rate of\nconvergence). We end by exploring lower order terms in families of elliptic\ncurves. We present evidence supporting a conjecture that the average second\nmoment in one-parameter families without complex multiplication has, when\nappropriately viewed, a negative bias, and end with a discussion of the\nconsequences of this bias on the distribution of low-lying zeros, in particular\nrelations between such a bias and the observed excess rank in families.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Feb 2016 15:23:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-03"}
